description: Lists the root or organizational units (OUs) that serve as the immediate parent of the specified child OU or account. This operation, along with  ListChildren enables you to traverse the tree structure that makes up this root. This operation can be called only from the organization's management account or by a member account that is a delegated administrator.

parameters.name: ChildId
parameters.description: The unique identifier (ID) of the OU or account whose parent containers you want to list. Don't specify a root. The regex pattern for a child ID string requires one of the following: Account - A string that consists of exactly 12 digits. Organizational unit (OU) - A string that begins with 'ou-' followed by from 4 to 32 lowercase letters or digits (the ID of the root that contains the OU). This string is followed by a second '-' dash and from 8 to 32 additional lowercase letters or digits.

nested_items.name: Parents
nested_items.description: A list of parents for the specified child account or OU.

nested_items.name: Id
nested_items.description: The unique identifier (ID) of the parent entity.

nested_items.name: Type
nested_items.description: The type of the parent entity.

nested_items.name: NextToken
nested_items.description: If present, indicates that more output is available than is included in the current response. Use this value in the NextToken request parameter in a subsequent call to the operation to get the next part of the output. You should repeat this until the NextToken response element comes back as null.
